Rating: 3
This was easy and delicious! The mint helps take away some of the egg smell--I always use it in frittatas. Like another reviewer, I too bought the mushrooms from the farmer's market and used fresh mint from our garden. This simple dish is wonderful for Sunday lunch, I will certainly make again.

Rating: 4
I used 2 T of butter in addition to the olive oil and I added one more clove of garlic. I just happened to have 3/4 lb of wild mushrooms just purchased from the Farmer's Market. This was delicious and everybody in my house loved it. I served it with some crusty bread.

Rating: 1
Totally blah. I put in less mushrooms than called for and more salt, and I added cracked black pepper, and it was still boring. The mushrooms seemed to completely overpower the mint and you couldn't even taste it. I thought this dish was ok but definitely wouldn't make it again. My husband, who is usually easy to please, didn't finish his portion and ate something else for the rest of his dinner. It was easy to make, at least.

Rating: 3
So easy to make and really delicious. I would never have thought to mix mint with mushroom. Makes a great lunch or light supper with some crusty bread or fruit or salad. I have made this several times, substituting basil for mint one time and that was delicious as well. Any easy lunch you can whip up in minutes!

