Excellent - I used dried chanterelles and fresh crimini, and served it on a bed of greens with a simple dressing of olive oil, lemon, oregano, salt and pepper. A fresh, but filling, first course. Sancerre or a crisp Italian white.

Rating: 2
This frittata turned out ok. It wasn't bad, but it wasn't great. 1 pound of mushrooms for this recipe is ridiculous. I used 3/4 pounds wild mushrooms, and it was still too much. I suggest using 1/2 pound of mushrooms, 3 garlic cloves, and 1 teaspoon of salt. Use the mint as a garnish in the end, as the cooking process takes away a lot of its flavor. Don't over sautee, or the eggs might stick to the pan when you try to take the frittata out.